Product Availability Monitoring
https://app.opus.com/app/workflow/share/264a3329-5d5a-4040-a5b5-3551d8fe15bf


This workflow checks the availability of a product on a specified web page and sends a notification to the user
when the product is detected as in stock. It retrieves the product page content, extracts visible text, 
determines stock status based on predefined keywords, generates a notification message if the product is available,
and delivers the notification using the user's preferred contact method.

Industry
Retail & E-commerce - E-commerce Platform Administration
Inputs 
The web address (URL) that points directly to a specific product page.

A list of keywords or phrases that indicate a product is out of stock.

The preferred channel for sending the notification (e.g., email, sms, push).

The contact details for delivering the notification.
Output
Indicates whether the notification was successfully sent to the user.
